# badges
Here you can find lots of _ugly_ badge combinations I made for fun or for some open-source projects. 

Most of them are powered with Base64 encoded logos, and only rely on Github or Shields backends, so it should be safe.

These are very long strings so just open the raw version of the hereby README file and copy the Markdown code of the badge you want.

```markdown
![badge title](https://img.shields.io/badge/label-status-hexcolor?logo=data:image/png;base64,...)
```
